🧠 VECTOR DATABASE — COMPLETE WORKFLOW (INPUT → OUTPUT)
🔥 0. Big Picture (don’t skip this)

System has 3 core parts:

Embedding Model → converts text to vector
Vector DB → stores & searches vectors
LLM (optional) → generates final answer

  ⚙️ 1. DATA INGESTION (Storing your data)
Step 1: Raw Data Input
You start with:
PDFs / Docs / Text / Website / Database
Example:   "Our refund policy lasts 7 days..."


Step 2: Chunking (VERY IMPORTANT)
👉 You don’t store full documents.
You split into smaller pieces:
Chunk 1: "Our refund policy lasts 7 days"
Chunk 2: "No refund after 7 days."
Why?
Embeddings work better on small chunks
Improves search accuracy
👉 If you skip this → garbage results


Step 3: Convert Text → Embeddings
Each chunk goes into the embedding model
Chunk → Embedding Model → Vector
Example:
"Our refund policy lasts 7 days."
→ [0.12, -0.88, 0.45, ...]



Step 4: Store in Vector DB
Now store:
{
  vector: [0.12, -0.88, 0.45, ...],
  metadata: {
    text: "Our refund policy lasts 7 days",
    source: "refund_doc.pdf"
  }
}
}

👉 This is key:
Vector = for search
Metadata = for returning actual content



Step 5: User Input
User: "What is your refund policy?"


Step 6: Convert Query → Vector
Same embedding model:
Query → Embedding → Vector
Example:
"What is your refund policy?"
→ [0.10, -0.85, 0.40, ...]



Step 7: Similarity Search (CORE of vector DB)
Now vector DB does:
👉 “Find closest vectors to this query vector”
Using math like:
cosine similarity
dot product


Step 8: Retrieve Top Matches
Example result:
1. "Our refund policy lasts 7 days"
2. "No refund after 7 days"
👉 These are the most relevant chunks


Step 9: Send to LLM (RAG)
Now you combine:
User Query + Retrieved Chunks
Example:
Context:
"Our refund policy lasts 7 days"

Question:
"What is your refund policy?"



Step 10: LLM Generates Answer
LLM outputs:
"Our refund policy allows refunds within 7 days of purchase."
🔁 FULL PIPELINE (ONE VIEW — SAVE THIS)
[DATA INGESTION]
Raw Data
→ Chunking
→ Embedding Model
→ Vectors
→ Store in Vector DB (with metadata)


[QUERY PHASE]

User Query
→ Embedding Model
→ Query Vector
→ Similarity Search in Vector DB
→ Retrieve Top K Results


[RESPONSE PHASE]

Retrieved Context
→ Send to LLM
→ Final Answer
